E-VotePro Electronic Voting System

Project Description
E-VotePro is an OOP based voting system in C++ that simulates elections with voters, candidates, admins, and auditors.

Features
Supports voting, eligibility checking, vote storage, election management, and audit verification. Includes file handling for data persistence.

Roles
Voter casts votes, Candidate views results, Admin manages elections, Auditor verifies vote integrity.

Architecture
Built using OOP principles including inheritance, polymorphism, abstraction, and encapsulation. Separate classes handle users, elections, authentication, and recommendations.

File Structure
Single main C++ file with candidates.csv and votes.csv for storage.

How to Run
Compile using g++ and run the executable. Use the menu to select roles and perform actions.

Security
Each vote is hashed and stored. Auditor verifies votes to detect tampering.

Future Improvements
Can be extended with database support, GUI, and stronger encryption.

Author
Academic C++ OOP project for learning system design and programming concepts.
